svcsubproc.para:
Data link circuits are used to transmit serial data transmissions between the ECM and other controllers in the system. This type of circuit carries the signals between the ECM, the ATA data link connector (discussed in
ATA DATA LINK CONNECTOR
) and also between the ECM and the vehicle speedometer and tachometer and between the ECM and the Antilock Brake/Traction system controller. The wires for these circuits will always be "twisted" together to protect the signals from interference.
